    <body style="background-color:black; font-size:150%; border: 2px solid white">
        <h1 style="color:white; font-family: garamond; text-align:center;">HTML Colours</h1>

        <hr>

        <h2 style="color:white; font-family: garamond;">HTML Colour Styles</h2>

        <p style="color:white; font-family: garamond;">
            HTML has Background Colour, Text Colour and Border Colour Styles.
        </p>

        <p style="color:white; font-family: garamond;">
            Colours ar expressed in various forms.<br>
            HTML recognizes 140 Standard Colour Names.<br>
        </p>

        <p style="color:white; font-family: garamond;">
            RGB Colour Values are expressed as "rgb(0-255, 0-255, 0-255)"<br>
            HEX Colour Values are expressed from '#000000' to '#ffffff'<br>
            HSL Colour Values are expressed as "hsl(0-100%, 0-100%, 0-100%)"<br>
        </p>

        <p style="color:white; font-family: garamond;">
            Both RGB and HSL Values Support Transparency Coefficient <em>Alpha</em> with an extension<br>
            "rgba(0-255, 0-255, 0-255, 0-1)" and "hsla(0-100%, 0-100%, 0-100%, 0-1)"
        </p><hr>

        <hr>

